Ah c&#x27;mon at least try a bit harder. &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;password&#x27;&#x27;&#x27; is defined as:<p><pre><code>   char password[LINE_MAX];
</code></pre>
So that&#x27;s preventing a buffer overflow and is perfectly fine.<p>LINE_MAX is a POSIX thing: <a href="http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/basedefs/limits.h.html" rel="nofollow">http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/basedefs/limi...</a><p>There&#x27;s no one putting a silly limit on password length there.<p>I worked that out in 2 mins flat. Bear in mind I haven&#x27;t even looked at the systemd source code before.<p>Edit: you know I&#x27;ve actually read some of that code and it&#x27;s pretty nice.
